                            server to integrate &jax-ws.product.name; for
                            hosting JAX-WS services</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist></para>
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
                <para>Endpoint Deployment <itemizedlist>
                        <listitem>
                            <para><link
                            xlink:href="http://glassfish.java.net">Glassfish
                            v3</link> <itemizedlist>
                                    <listitem>
                                        <para>Tightly integrated with Glassfish</para>
                                    </listitem>

                                    <listitem>
                                        <para>Supports EJB and Web endpoints</para>
                                    </listitem>

                                    <listitem>
                                        <para>109 based deployment support for better
                                        portability</para>
                                    </listitem>

                                    <listitem>
                                        <para>JAX-WS RI specific deployment descriptor
                                        support</para>
                                    </listitem>
                                </itemizedlist></para>
                        </listitem>

                        <listitem>
                            <para><link
                            xlink:href="http://www.sun.com/software/products/appsrvr_pe/index.xml">Sun
                            One Application Server 9.0 ur1</link></para>
                        </listitem>

                        <listitem>
                            <para>Light weight HTTP server <itemizedlist>
                                    <listitem>
                                        <para>Bundled with JDK 6</para>
                                    </listitem>
                                </itemizedlist></para>
                        </listitem>

                        <listitem>
                            <para>Any other container that supports Servlet 2.4,
                            such as Tomcat, Jetty, Geronimo, JBoss, Resin, ...
                            You name it!</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist></para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>

        <para>This release brings in the highly pluggable framework through
        abstractions such as <link
        xlink:href="http://jax-ws-architecture-document.java.net/nonav/doc21/com/sun/xml/ws/api/pipe/Tube.html">Tube</link>
        and <link
        xlink:href="http://jax-ws-architecture-document.java.net/nonav/doc21/com/sun/xml/ws/api/message/Message.html">Message</link>.
        This architecture document is a glorified javadoc which includes all
        the JAX-WS RI specific APIs. &jax-ws.product.name; has many bug fixes
        made for interoperability with .NET 3.0. This is made mostly possible
        due to WSIT, which uses JAX-WS plugabble architecture to plug in
        support for WS-Metadata, WS-Policy, WS-ReliableMessaging,
        WS-Transaction, WS-SecureConversation and WS-Security.</para>

        <para>If you wish to use &jax-ws.product.name; in a Java EE container
        in a Java EE portable manner you need to use the standard Java EE 6
        deployment descriptor; please refer to the <link
        xlink:href="http://java.sun.com/javaee/index.jsp">Java EE 6</link> or
        <link xlink:href="http://glassfish.java.net/">Glassfish</link>
        documentation/samples. The majority of the documentation included with
        JAX-WS is valid with Java EE 6 as well.</para>
    </section>

